LEGIONELLOSIS, SUSTAINED TRANSMISSION - USA (ARIZONA, OHIO)(02)
===============================================================
[see
Legionellosis, sustained transmission - USA (Ariz... 970516174534]
[1]
Date: Mon, 19 May 1997 10:00:24 -0600
From: Dennis Ostermiller <LODOSTER@ihc.com>
Do you think we should initiate a periodic sampling of our cullinary water
for legionellosis? Our policy is to maintain 120 deg. water throughout the
facility except in peds and TCU which are at 110 deg.
We have had no previous indications of problems and do not have any hot
water storage tanks. Our water heaters are flow through design and heat the
water on demand. We also have a recirculating system which keeps most of the
piping with water circulating constantly rather than standing still. Let me
know what you think.
---
Dennis Ostermiller
