[3]
From: jsd4@WONDER.EM.CDC.GOV
Date: Mon, 19 May 97 12:23:00 EST
FROM: Duchin, Jeffrey

Regarding the diagnosis of legionellosis: the legionella urine antigen test
is both sensitive and specific in detecting serogroup 1 disease (70-90% of
all cases of legionellosis) and remains positive for weeks after infection.
This often neglected diagnostic test has great potential utility.
---
Jeff Duchin, M.D.
Seattle
